**Perfect Multicollinearity in Linear Regression.** Fit $Y \approx \beta_{0} + \beta_{1} x_{1} + \beta_{2} x_{2} + \beta_{3} z$ where $z = (x_{1}+x_{2})/2$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Is the OLS solution unique?

\item What happens to the coefficients and fitted values?

\item How should you fix the specification?\end{enumerate}
